  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [ ] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (153ae19 2022-06-26T00:04:15.775569508Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nThe nonce inside of scripts starts at 1, remains at 1 for the first broadcast, and then correctly increments for subsequent broadcasts. This means scripts cannot tell if an address has sent 0 or 1 txs which naturally causes issues.\r\n\r\nMinimal reproduction:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/proximacapital/forge-nonce-issue",
